ğŸ¯ Goal:

Make the Report Found Document page fully functional so users can fill out a form, and the data gets saved to the found_documents table in MySQL.

ğŸªœ Step 1: Create Table for Found Documents

Open phpMyAdmin â†’ your database (lost_doc_db) â†’ SQL tab
and paste this ğŸ‘‡

CREATE TABLE found_documents (
  id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(100),
  doc_type VARCHAR(50),
  doc_number VARCHAR(50),
  contact VARCHAR(100),
  description TEXT,
  date TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);


Click Go âœ…
Now the table is ready.

ğŸªœ Step 2: Create File for Reporting Found Documents

Inside your project folder, create a new file:
ğŸ“ report_found.php

Paste this code ğŸ‘‡

<?php include('includes/db_connect.php'); ?>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Report Found Document</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <h2>Report Found Document</h2>

  <form method="POST" action="">
    <label>Your Name:</label><br>
    <input type="text" name="name" required><br><br>

    <label>Document Type:</label><br>
    <input type="text" name="doc_type" placeholder="e.g. Citizenship, License, ID Card" required><br><br>

    <label>Document Number:</label><br>
    <input type="text" name="doc_number"><br><br>

    <label>Contact Information:</label><br>
    <input type="text" name="contact" placeholder="Phone, Email or Address" required><br><br>

    <label>Additional Description:</label><br>
    <textarea name="description" rows="4" placeholder="Where and when you found it..." required></textarea><br><br>

    <button type="submit" name="submit">Submit</button>
  </form>

  <?php
  if (isset($_POST['submit'])) {
      $name = $_POST['name'];
      $doc_type = $_POST['doc_type'];
      $doc_number = $_POST['doc_number'];
      $contact = $_POST['contact'];
      $description = $_POST['description'];

      $sql = "INSERT INTO found_documents (name, doc_type, doc_number, contact, description)
              VALUES ('$name', '$doc_type', '$doc_number', '$contact', '$description')";

      if ($conn->query($sql) === TRUE) {
          echo "<p style='color:green;'>Found document reported successfully!</p>";
      } else {
          echo "<p style='color:red;'>Error: " . $conn->error . "</p>";
      }
  }
  ?>
</body>
</html>

