ğŸªœ Step 4 (Optional â€“ show entries instantly)

Below the PHP code that handles the form, add this snippet to show all found entries immediately:

echo "<h3>All Reported Found Documents</h3>";
$result = $conn->query("SELECT * FROM found_documents ORDER BY id DESC");
if ($result->num_rows > 0) {
    echo "<table border='1' cellpadding='10'>
            <tr>
              <th>ID</th>
              <th>Name</th>
              <th>Document Type</th>
              <th>Number</th>
              <th>Contact</th>
              <th>Description</th>
              <th>Date</th>
            </tr>";
    while ($row = $result->fetch_assoc()) {
        echo "<tr>
                <td>{$row['id']}</td>
                <td>{$row['name']}</td>
                <td>{$row['doc_type']}</td>
                <td>{$row['doc_number']}</td>
                <td>{$row['contact']}</td>
                <td>{$row['description']}</td>
                <td>{$row['date']}</td>
              </tr>";
    }
    echo "</table>";
} else {
    echo "<p>No records yet.</p>";
}
